snippet.textDisplay:
Even the behind the scenes making of the Star Wars Trilogy is entertaining. I tried to watch the behind the scenes stuff of the Prequels but generally got bored when it was mainly watching actors shot behind green screen pretending to chop up invisible droids.

But that aside, I think that's why we need to move back towards practical effects. All the CGI stuff can be fine all small doses but don't overdo it and only try it if it's not possible with practical effects.
snippet.textOriginal:

snippet.textDisplay: Disagree about Star Wars being fantasy. It has some fantastical elements, but it's sci-fi. It's space, aliens, and regardless of being "a long time ago," it's futuristic technology. Sure there's the force, but that only loosely resembles magic, and many of things pulled off are not out of the realm of sci-fi (telekinesis, telepathy, etc.)
